rComments: Tough course but very smart guy. Makes you work hard.
Really bad prof, doesn't reply email at all

Avoid this prof if you can. He is a head of department so he has other things than you. He didn't post outline and material to study for the tests. He mainly reads from the slides which are bullet points. He gives examples mainly written in the content of a textbook. But he expects that you know all the material on the slides especially proofs.
The slides are all just listing points without any specific examples. Test and quiz are extremely hard.

Test are ridiculous. Who will remember the density function of Gamma Dustribution. He never mentions hows the test gonna be. Lectures are boring and it's really hard to follow. He didn't really explain concepts or give any examples. The slides are also not very useful. Go to other section if you can.

Lectures are hard to follow. The lecture slides he provides in the lecture are quite sparse, with point notes about concepts, but he doesn't delve very much into them, and doesn't provide many examples. Seems kind of unprepared for lectures overall, and almost always ends them early.

Extremely unclear in lectures. Talks on and on about vague concepts but show close to no examples at all. Always end class early and when you ask questions after class the response is "Come to my office hours".
